The paper deals with the study of channels and their properties, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The concepts of input-degradedness and input-equivalence are also related to probability theory and stochastic processes, which are often studied in the context of information theory (cs.ITP). The paper also discusses the construction of topologies on the space of input-equivalent channels, which is a topic in topology and geometry (cs.SI). Additionally, the study of channel parameters and operations under these topologies involves the use of statistical and machine learning techniques (cs.MM), and the investigation of the properties of these topologies can be seen as a problem in mathematical analysis (cs.LG).
